Note:
compiler/frontend/lexical/operators.runa
Operator Definitions and Tokenization

This module provides comprehensive operator functionality including:
- Natural language operators ("plus", "multiplied by", "is equal to")
- Technical syntax operators (+, *, ==) for --developer mode
- Mathematical symbol operators (≤, ≥, ≠, ≈, etc.)
- Operator precedence and associativity management
- Context-sensitive operator recognition
- Dual syntax mode operator conversion
- Performance optimized operator matching
- Integration with mathematical symbol processing
:End Note

Import "dev/debug/errors/core" as Errors

Note: =====================================================================
Note: OPERATOR DATA STRUCTURES
Note: =====================================================================

Type called "OperatorInfo":
    operator_symbol as String
    natural_form as String
    technical_form as String
    precedence as Integer
    associativity as String
    category as String
    arity as Integer
    is_mathematical as Boolean

Type called "OperatorMap":
    natural_operators as Dictionary[String, OperatorInfo]
    technical_operators as Dictionary[String, OperatorInfo]
    mathematical_operators as Dictionary[String, OperatorInfo]
    precedence_table as Dictionary[String, Integer]

Type called "OperatorRecognizer":
    recognizer_id as String
    operator_map as OperatorMap
    current_mode as String
    statistics as Dictionary[String, Integer]

